Designation: Triton Machine Works' H.M.S. Crusader<br>
<br>
<br>
<a href="images/crusader/cruspose.jpg">
<img src="images/crusader/small/cruspose_small1.jpg" border=0 alt="The HMS Crusader" width="100" height="75" align="right"></a>With the new influx of Senate funding, the 'Corps
    has been able to begin extended tests of advanced hardware. Alongside the<a href="kite.html"> Kite</a> and a new
    medium mech, the <a href="kodiak.html">Kodiak</a>, the 'Corps has expressed interest in the new Highly Mobile Suit from Triton
    Machine Works. The HMS Crusader Mk1 is far and away the most advanced infantry suit to
    date. New reactive joint technology from Sproat Industries and improved composite armor
    forming processes are only the two most obvious improvements.
</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><a href="images/crusader/crusopen.jpg"><img src="images/crusader/small/crusopen_small1.jpg" border=0 alt="The Crusader's open canopy." width="100" height="75" align="right"></a>With the coming of the McMillan armor process, armor
    can be formed into single unit rather than being joined as in the past. With a greater
    ability to form complex shapes, the armor can be extended farther to more completely
    protect the pilot. Leaving the pilot's head more exposed allows for greater
      visiblility.
    To compensate, the canopy has been designed and cast to withstand impacts from projectiles
    up to 3cm. In addition, the canopy is gilded to withstand up to a class 4 energy weapon,
    approximately on the scale of a truck mounted laser cannon.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      <hr>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><a href="images/crusader/crusbeam.jpg"><img src="images/crusader/small/crusbeam_small1.jpg" border=0 alt width="100" height="75" align="right"></a>Carrying a large loadout of weapons has become the
    norm for 'Corps units due to the necessity of operating in small squads. The Crusader
    carries a large twin beam cannon. This particular cannon design is rather unique. The
    cannon barrels themselves are recessed behind a reinforced ramming head. With this
    reinforcement, the Crusader can use it's left arm as a very effective demolition and close
    combat tool. Almost as an afterthought, the top of the forearm, near the elbow, houses a
    small smartstick launcher. Carrying only 25 rounds, the launcher still broadens the
    Crusader's attack envelope.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
